{"parse":{"title":"Slow science","pageid":11045901,"revid":854392530,"text":{"*":"<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><p class=\"mw-empty-elt\">\n</p><p><b>Slow science</b> is part of the broader <a href=\"/wiki/Slow_movement_(culture)\" title=\"Slow movement (culture)\">slow movement</a>. It is based on the belief that <a href=\"/wiki/Science\" title=\"Science\">science</a> should be a slow, steady, methodical process, and that scientists should not be expected to provide \"quick fixes\" to society's problems. Slow science supports <a href=\"/wiki/Curiosity\" title=\"Curiosity\">curiosity</a>-driven <a href=\"/wiki/Scholarly_method\" title=\"Scholarly method\">scientific research</a> and opposes <a href=\"/wiki/Performance_measurement\" title=\"Performance measurement\">performance targets</a>.\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"See_also\">See also</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Slow_science&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" title=\"Edit section: See also\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div role=\"navigation\" aria-label=\"Portals\" class=\"noprint portal plainlist tright\" style=\"margin:0.5em 0 0.5em 1em;border:solid #aaa 1px\">\n<ul style=\"display:table;box-sizing:border-box;padding:0.1em;max-width:175px;background:#f9f9f9;font-size:85%;line-height:110%;font-style:italic;font-weight:bold\">\n<li style=\"display:table-row\"><span style=\"display:table-cell;padding:0.2em;vertical-align:middle;text-align:center\"><a href=\"/wiki/File:Nuvola_apps_kalzium.svg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"icon\" src=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/8/8b/Nuvola_apps_kalzium.svg/28px-Nuvola_apps_kalzium.svg.png\" width=\"28\" height=\"28\" class=\"noviewer\" srcset=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/8/8b/Nuvola_apps_kalzium.svg/42px-Nuvola_apps_kalzium.svg.png 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/8/8b/Nuvola_apps_kalz